  "prompt": "Is it forbidden in Islam to name your child Allah?",
  "response": "In Islam, it is generally considered inappropriate to name a child \"Allah\" because Allah is the unique name of God in Islam, and is not to be used as a personal name for individuals. Many scholars and Islamic authorities advise against using divine names in this manner, as it can lead to misunderstandings about the oneness of God and His attributes. Instead, Muslims are encouraged to choose names that have positive meanings and are in line with Islamic teachings. Always, it is best to consult with a knowledgeable person or authority in your community if you have specific questions about naming practices.",
